That said, there are real issues and missing defenses worth addressing.

---

## Findings

### 1. Sensitive data exposure (PII) on an unauthenticated endpoint — Medium
**OWASP A01: Broken Access Control / A02: Cryptographic Failures (sensitive data exposure)**

`GET /users` (lines 11–16) returns user emails with no authentication or authorization. Even with hardcoded demo data, this pattern is dangerous because it ships to production unchanged.

```js
