### 5. A09: Security Logging & Monitoring Failures — No request logging or error handling (Medium)

There is no logger and no error-handling middleware. Unhandled errors in Express default to a stack trace in the response in development mode, which leaks internals (A05).

**Recommendation:**
```js
const morgan = require('morgan');
app.use(morgan('combined'));

// 404
app.use((req, res) => res.status(404).json({ error: 'not found' }));

// Central error handler — must be last and have 4 args
app.use((err, req, res, _next) => {
  console.error({ msg: 'unhandled', err: err.message, stack: err.stack });
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'internal error' });
});
```

### 6. A05: Security Misconfiguration — No body-size limits / parsers configured defensively (Low, preemptive)

No body parsers are used today, but when `express.json()` is added, cap the payload size to prevent memory-exhaustion DoS:

