  const users = getUsers().map(u => ({ id: u.id, name: u.name })); // no email unless authorized
  res.json(users);
});
```

### 4. No CORS policy defined (OWASP A05) — **Latent issue**
Express has no default CORS headers, so cross-origin browser reads are currently blocked — which is actually safe. But teams often reach for `app.use(cors())` (wildcard) the first time a frontend complains. Decide the policy explicitly now:
```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: ['https://your-frontend.example.com'], methods: ['GET'] }));
```

### 5. Unconditional `app.listen` on require (OWASP A05) — **Testability/robustness**
`app.listen(3000, ...)` runs at import time, which means `require('./app')` (including in tests) binds port 3000 and logs. Separate the app from the server:
```js
