// server.js
const app = require('./app');
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
```
This also removes the hardcoded port (minor configuration smell).

### 6. `console.log` as the only observability (OWASP A09: Security Logging and Monitoring Failures) — **Real for production**
No structured logging, no request log, no error handler. You won't detect abuse. Add a structured logger and a final error handler:
```js
