## Findings

### 1. No authentication on PII-returning endpoint — **High**
**OWASP:** A01:2021 Broken Access Control / A04 Insecure Design

`GET /users` (lines 11–16) returns user records including **email addresses** (PII) to any unauthenticated caller. Even though the data is hardcoded today, the endpoint shape is the template future code will follow.

**Recommendation:** gate it behind auth middleware and only return fields the caller is authorized to see.

```js
const requireAuth = (req, res, next) => {
  const token = req.headers.authorization?.replace(/^Bearer\s+/i, '');
  if (!token || !verifyJwt(token)) return res.sendStatus(401);
  req.user = decodeJwt(token);
  next();
};

app.get('/users', requireAuth, (req, res) => {
